			<ns0:name>dsprin...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112723007196297768207/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The old ucontext.h API has been deprecated on the Mac in OS X 10.6.  It looks like we should migrate to the Grand Central Dispatch APIs, see e.g. this blog:

https://groups.google.com/group/comp.sys.mac.programmer.help/browse_thread/thread/5135ddb9f397aa71?pli=1

As a work-around nacl_signals.h can #include &amp;lt;sys/ucontext.h&amp;gt; but there is no guarantee that the deprecated APIs will work on the Mac in 10.6 and later.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-03-17T19:55:38.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-10-13T20:20:49.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
